sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant KRBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS (reencrypt)
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Rest as rest-container<br/>8080/TCP HTTP (localhost)
    participant PG as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP

    Note over Client,PG: Flow 1: Model Registry API Request (with kube-rbac-proxy)

    Client->>Router: HTTPS/443<br/>TLS 1.2+
    Router->>KRBAC: HTTPS/8443<br/>TLS (reencrypt)<br/>OpenShift serving cert
    KRBAC->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>HTTPS/443<br/>ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>KRBAC: Auth decision (allow/deny)
    KRBAC->>Rest: HTTP/8080 (localhost)<br/>Pre-authorized
    Rest->>PG: TCP/5432<br/>Optional SSL<br/>Username/password
    PG-->>Rest: Query results
    Rest-->>KRBAC: JSON response
    KRBAC-->>Router: HTTPS response
    Router-->>Client: HTTPS response

    Note over Client,PG: Flow 2: ModelRegistry CR Reconciliation

    participant Op as Operator Controller

    K8sAPI->>Op: Watch notification<br/>ModelRegistry CR change<br/>HTTPS/TLS 1.2+
    Op->>K8sAPI: HTTPS/443<br/>ServiceAccount token<br/>Create/Update resources
    Note over Op: Creates: Deployment, Service,<br/>ServiceAccount, RBAC,<br/>Route, NetworkPolicy

    Note over Client,PG: Flow 3: Model Catalog Data Initialization

    participant InitCatalog as catalog-data-init<br/>(init container)
    participant InitBench as benchmark-data-init<br/>(init container)
    participant Catalog as model-catalog<br/>container
    participant CatPG as Catalog PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP

    InitCatalog->>InitCatalog: Copy model metadata YAML<br/>to shared emptyDir
    InitBench->>InitBench: Copy benchmark data<br/>to shared emptyDir
    Catalog->>Catalog: Read catalog sources<br/>from ConfigMap + shared data
    Catalog->>CatPG: TCP/5432<br/>Username/password<br/>from Secret env vars
    CatPG-->>Catalog: Data stored
